ðŸŸ© Problem
- You need to evaluate a mathematical expression containing + - * /.  
- Numbers can be multi-digit.  
- Multiplication and division must happen before addition and subtraction.  
- Division truncates toward zero.

Use stack to evaluate mathematical expression and return the result.


ðŸŸ© Sample Input : (A single string representing mathematical expression to be evaluated)
3+5/2

ðŸŸ© Sample Output : (integer value representing the result of the evaluated expression)
5

ðŸŸ© Solution (Array used as Stack)

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.nextLine();

        int[] arr = new int[s.length()];
        int top = -1;

        int num = 0;
        char sign = '+';

        s = s + "+";

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char ch = s.charAt(i);

            if (Character.isDigit(ch)) {
                num = num * 10 + (ch - '0');
            } 
            else if (ch == '+' || ch == '-' || ch == '*' || ch == '/') {

                if (sign == '+') {
                    arr[++top] = num;
                } else if (sign == '-') {
                    arr[++top] = -num;
                } else if (sign == '*') {
                    arr[top] = arr[top] * num;
                } else if (sign == '/') {
                    arr[top] = arr[top] / num;
                }

                sign = ch;
                num = 0;
            }
        }

        int ans = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i <= top; i++) {
            ans += arr[i];
        }

        System.out.print(ans);
    }
}

ðŸŸ© Time Complexity - O(n) â€” each character scanned once
ðŸŸ© Space Complexity -O(n) â€” stack stores partial values in worst case
